@node "Copying" "Copying"

@{u}@{b}Copying@{uu}@{ub}

    SysPic 4.00, unlike previous versions, is relased under the concept of
@{"SHAREWARE" link Register}.  It can be freely distributed under following conditions:

    @{b}1.@{ub} Everything in this distribution must be kept together and
       unaltered.

    @{b}2.@{ub} Copyright notices are not removed from executable and
       documentation.

    @{b}3.@{ub} No more than a nominal fee is charged to cover cost of magnetic
       media.

    @{b}4.@{ub} Magazines are allowed to include the SysPic on a coverdisk
       but have to send a free copy of the issue to the author.

@{b}SysPic is Copyright (C) 1995-1996 The Beet Research.
                        All rights reserved.
@{ub}
@endnode

@node "Shareware" "Shareware"

@{u}@{b}SHAREWARE@{uu}@{ub}

    The SysPic is @{b}SHAREWARE@{ub}.  This does not mean it is free.  If you want to
use  it on regular basis you have to register, after one month of evaluation
period.   The  program  is not crippled in any way, but displays a shareware
reminder when quits.  The registration fee is only

                               @{b}US$10@{ub} or @{b}15 DEM@{ub}

which  I  consider  very  reasonable.  Read @{"how to register" link Register}.

    After registration I send you back a disk with the latest SysPic release
along with the personalized keyfile which will remove the annoying shareware
reminder.   Alternatively  I can send the keyfile via E-mail.  Once you have
the  keyfile, you will be @{b}"set for life"@{ub} where updates are concearned.  This
means you will not have pay more even for SysPic 9.00 :) @{u}You cannot give the
keyfile to anybody else!@{uu}

    Using  the  program  after  the evaluation period without registering is
both  illegal and immoral.  Even more illegal is using SysPic with a cracked
keyfile.  In case you have got an illegal keyfile, send it to me.  If you're
the  first  who  sent me that one, you will get a FREE one for yourself as a
reward.   The  piracy  is mostly responsible for killing the Amiga.  Please,
help fighting it!

    @{b}IMPORTANT  NOTE:@{ub}   all people who registered previous versions of SysPic
by  sending  me  a  postcard  will get the keyfile FOR FREE.  You are listed
@{"here" link Acknow 100}.  If you want to get the keyfile via Snail send me a disk.  Well, this
is  a  lesson  for those, who ignored cardware or were just too lazy.  Think
twice next time.

    Well,  why  to  pay  the  fee?   Not  because  I  spend much time on the
programming.   I'm  really devoted Amiga programmer and it's pleasure for me
to  support  our  beloved  computer.   If  I  would  be  in a good financial
situation,  the  SysPic  would  have remain freeware.  But I'm not.  Well, I
don't  think  I'll get rich because of making SysPic shareware.  I am a poor
Polish  student.   My  mother, who is a teacher...  gets about $200 a month.
Yeah,  it's the goverment attitude to the education.  And believe me, prices
in  Poland  doesn't  differ much from those in West European countries, some
are even higher (like computer equipment's).

    I really hope you won't hesitate to register.  @{b}Thank you in advance!@{ub}
@endnode

